replies.body:
The new Abyssal Mask seems to fill a very long-term gap in itemization, specifically a tanky mana + MR item that works as a rush item on champs like {{champion:79}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:57}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:113}} {{champion:32}} {{champion:27}} 

It also seems like a very strong option for certain mages in extremely bad matchups - the kind of matchups where you win lane by not feeding the Syndra (for example). Or as a single mid/late defensive item versus low-counterplay threats like Zac or Veigar ult.

To me, the new Mask seems insanely slot efficient with the mix of hp, mana, sustain, resist, CDR, and +10% magic damage. **In testing did it seem as strong as it looks on paper? Which champs are the biggest winners and losers with this item?** (Singed seems like a huge winner since he has a rushable item against some of his biggest counters)

Demon pants...
